Nitzan Bukchin (208939405), David Harvith (206124281)  
EX: 3

FILES:  
- MapReduceFramework.cpp -- Implementation of the MapReduce framework API.  
- GeneralContext.h -- Declaration of internal context structures. 
- GeneralContext.cpp -- Definitions for job-wide and per-thread state.  
- Barrier.h -- Declaration of the Barrier class.  
- Barrier.cpp -- Implementation of the Barrier class for thread synchronization.  
- errors.h -- Error message constants.  
- Makefile -- Builds libMapReduceFramework.a from all .cpp sources.

REMARKS:  
- Each thread performs Map → Sort, waits at a barrier,  
  then thread 0 performs Shuffle, and all threads perform Reduce.  
- emit2 and emit3 are implemented as required.  
- Progress reporting is implemented using a packed 64-bit atomic variable.  
- The framework starts in UNDEFINED_STAGE and transitions correctly.  
- A per-job mutex is used for join to ensure thread safety and avoid global locks.

